Dialogue: 10,0:00:31.74,0:00:37.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,June 12th, 1956.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:37.01,0:00:40.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The 4th House of Councillors election was announced,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.38,0:00:45.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and six candidates were nominated by the Soka Gakkai: Kiyohara Katsu for the Tokyo district,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:45.10,0:00:47.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Haruki Seichiro for the Osaka district,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:47.80,0:00:51.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,as well as Seki Hisao, Harayama Koichi,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:51.22,0:00:56.04,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamadaira Chuhei, and Jujo Shunzo \Nfor the national district.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:56.04,0:00:58.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Kansai comrades, \Nwho proved their strength
Dialogue: 10,0:00:58.27,0:01:00.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,in the people’s victory \Nduring the May battle {of propagation}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:00.85,0:01:04.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and laid the firm groundwork \Nfor “Invincible Kansai,”
Dialogue: 10,0:01:04.32,0:01:07.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,have now thrown themselves wholeheartedly into campaigning
Dialogue: 10,0:01:07.55,0:01:11.47,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to secure candidate Haruki the top seat \Nin the House of Councillors election.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:13.69,0:01:18.50,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On this day, Josei Toda, who had been traveling around the country to encourage members,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:18.50,0:01:24.25,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,arrived to Osaka where his beloved disciple \NYamamoto Shinichi was in charge.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:24.25,0:01:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,To put politics back into the hands of the people, \NI recommended you to pick from our ranks
Dialogue: 10,0:01:29.74,0:01:34.91,Default,,0,0,0,,virtuous and capable distinguished citizens \Nto represent our ideals... {政治を民衆の手に取り戻すために 我が同志の中から高潔にして有能な人材を送ろうと皆で推薦したわけだが･･･}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:35.35,0:01:38.54,Thought,,0,0,0,,"Virtuous and capable distinguished citizens."
Dialogue: 10,0:01:38.54,0:01:43.35,Thought,,0,0,0,,This is the very essence and purpose \Nof Soka Gakkai's entry into politics.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:43.35,0:01:47.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei already outlined it before \Nat the Suikokai meeting.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:47.13,0:01:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Once in political power, a person {episode 12 25:36}
Dialogue: 10,0:01:50.35,0:01:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,is apt to succumb to its lurking demons \Nthat parasitize on the general public.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.43,0:02:04.19,Top,,0,0,0,,Please strive to become virtuous, capable men who reject self-interest. {ep12 26:10}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:04.19,0:02:12.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Live among the people, fight for them, \Nand spend your final days by their side.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:12.03,0:02:13.94,Thought,,0,0,0,,And also that...
Dialogue: 10,0:02:13.94,0:02:18.99,Top,,0,0,0,,Our political philosophy doesn’t align with either capitalism or socialism. {ep13 17:08}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:18.99,0:02:22.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, it is a centrist humanism \Ngrounded in the precepts of Buddhism.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:24.17,0:02:29.21,Default,,0,0,0,,To apply these ideals to people-oriented politics, we must enter the Diet,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:29.21,0:02:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the nation’s highest decision-making body,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:33.07,0:02:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and reform the political world from within to abolish politics driven by internal party agendas.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:39.35,0:02:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Japanese politics is currently \Nin a state of disarray that cannot be ignored.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:43.77,0:02:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we must make haste.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.46,0:02:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,In Osaka, a city of the common people \Nin the Kansai region, {ep13 16:25}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:49.63,0:02:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to start a peaceful revolution that will return politics to the hands of the people.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.63,0:03:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to reiterate it once more: campaigning must be carried out fair and square.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:00.06,0:03:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You must never force it on anyone
Dialogue: 10,0:03:01.91,0:03:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,or get so carried away that it turns destructive or breaks the law.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:06.71,0:03:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Fight with dignity and honor until the end\Nand let's win this House of Councillors election!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:12.88,0:03:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you do it, my friends?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.07,0:03:16.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:15.07,0:03:16.35,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:16.97,0:03:20.20,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With each passing day, \Nthe election campaign
Dialogue: 10,0:03:20.20,0:03:24.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was becoming more and more intense and it was finally entering the final stages.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:25.90,0:03:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:27.08,0:03:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, good morning!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:50.04,0:03:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Our situation is the same. {as this in the scriptures}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.21,0:03:55.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We're just one last push away \Nfrom admiring the moon over the capital.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.97,0:03:58.66,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a watershed moment!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:58.66,0:04:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s steel ourselves, \Nshake off all complacency,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.62,0:04:06.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and fight with unshakable faith \Nand full resolve to the very end!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:06.41,0:04:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:07.02,0:04:13.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If we lose after coming this far, we’ll let down the people of Osaka who put their trust in us.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:13.18,0:04:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But we'll never let that happen!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:16.40,0:04:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Losing is not an option! \NLet's win with confidence!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:20.28,0:04:21.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:21.49,0:04:25.59,Default,,0,0,0,,To drive Osaka’s growth \Nas a city of the people,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:25.59,0:04:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I plan to reform the tax system \Nwith fairness in mind,
Dialogue: 10,0:04:29.50,0:04:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,giving small and mid-sized businesses \Na real chance to thrive.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:33.88,0:04:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll fight tooth and nail for you!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:36.94,0:04:39.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Haruki-san, good luck!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:39.39,0:04:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget your promises \Nwhen you get there!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:42.57,0:04:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,There sure are a lot pf people waving to us.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:45.26,0:04:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They’re going out of their way \Nto give us a warm welcome. {lit: the response/reaction is transmitted tightly/stickily}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:47.89,0:04:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief was right. If we keep doing this, \Nit might just work out!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:51.85,0:04:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Haruki Seichiro will channel the fighting spirit \Nhe honed on the baseball field
Dialogue: 10,0:04:56.40,0:05:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,to make sure everyone's voices \Nare heard in politics!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.30,0:05:03.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Good! You have my vote!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:03.95,0:05:10.47,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The voting day came on July 8th, \Nand the vote count took place the next day.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.66,0:05:14.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Please listen to the noon news.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:15.37,0:05:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The vote counting for yesterday’s House \Nof Councillors election is proceeding smoothly.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:21.36,0:05:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,As of 11:30 a.m., here’s the latest vote count for the Osaka districts.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:25.94,0:05:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Sato Yoshiaki, Liberal Democratic Party, \N298,750 votes—elected. {/a pass}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:32.37,0:05:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Tsubaki Shigeo, Social Democrats, \N215,760 votes—elected.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:38.81,0:05:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Haruki Seichiro, non-partisan,\N194,860—confirmed elected. {/independent candidate}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:45.38,0:05:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Confirmed as elected!\NWe did it! I won! {sure to be elected; home free}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:49.88,0:05:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We won! Won!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:52.13,0:05:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank god!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:53.17,0:05:56.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,Now we're finally worthy of Sensei's support. {/lived up to sensei's hopes}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:56.29,0:06:00.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'm truly glad to share this joy \Nwith our Kansai comrades.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:00.67,0:06:04.20,Thought,,0,0,0,,But what worries me is Tokyo.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:04.20,0:06:08.13,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei said it might develop into \Na losing battle for us...
Dialogue: 10,0:06:08.13,0:06:10.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Against all odds, candidate Haruki
Dialogue: 10,0:06:10.51,0:06:15.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,secured third place in the fiercely contested Osaka district House of Councillors race,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:15.67,0:06:19.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,where only three seats were up for grabs.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:19.11,0:06:23.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Everyone said it was impossible, \Nbut now it was reality.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:23.34,0:06:27.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was, in every sense, a victory \Nthat made the impossible possible.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:27.72,0:06:31.32,Narrator,,0,0,0,,National constituency candidates Seki and Jujo were also elected,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:31.32,0:06:35.88,Narrator,,0,0,0,,bringing Soka Gakkai’s total to three seats \Nin the House of Councillors.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:38.26,0:06:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm finally back!
Dialogue: 10,0:06:39.37,0:06:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, welcome back! You've made good use of that long business trip.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:45.64,0:06:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Your support at every stage of our struggle \Nis what made the victory in Osaka possible.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:51.70,0:06:53.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:53.10,0:06:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations. Isn't it great?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:55.90,0:07:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Tokyo, which should not have lost, lost, \Nand Osaka, which should not have won, won.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:01.70,0:07:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems Tokyo needs to be reminded of the fundamentals of faith. {やはり東京は根本の信心がずれていたんだな}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:05.97,0:07:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We got careless and started going through \Nthe motions, so our efforts had no real impact. {lit: negligence was born, so we started doing all our activities without touching the ground (meaning "became elated and carried away"), so they ended up slipping by}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:11.41,0:07:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But I’m really glad Osaka pulled through, Shin-chan. That was one heck of a fight.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:17.06,0:07:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much for your hard work.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.13,0:07:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No, don't mention it.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:22.44,0:07:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,More importantly, \Nthe public is probably shocked right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:25.74,0:07:29.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You can bet the media’s \Ngoing to whip up another storm.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:29.74,0:07:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We must stay perfectly calm—\Nthere’s nothing to fear. {having presence of mind; self-possessed; imperturbable; calm and self-possessed​}
Dialogue: 10,0:07:39.83,0:07:44.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,What had once been a fringe religious group now had three representatives in the Diet—
Dialogue: 10,0:07:44.69,0:07:47.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the media jumped \Non the shocking election results
Dialogue: 10,0:07:47.99,0:07:52.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and kept churning out articles full of criticism and slander against the Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:52.63,0:07:57.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,They were all shallow, misguided, and thrown together for amusement—
Dialogue: 10,0:07:57.44,0:08:03.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but to Toda, it was clear that a larger, entrenched power stood behind them,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:03.96,0:08:06.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,swaying public opinion.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:10.12,0:08:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin-chan, there are still many steep mountains ahead on the journey of the Common Path.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:15.87,0:08:20.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay sharp, plant your feet with purpose, \Nand move forward carefully. {lit: when you have to hit with a hand, hit hard/firmly}
Dialogue: 10,0:08:20.83,0:08:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes—I’d be glad to walk that path with you.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:23.52,0:08:29.15,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,August: To prepare for the rapid spread of the Common Path and a surge in new members,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:29.15,0:08:37.06,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,a sweeping organizational reform was launched, establishing 16 new branches nationwide
Dialogue: 10,0:08:37.06,0:08:42.69,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The number of branches has doubled to 32, \Nand a nationwide system was established,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:42.69,0:08:45.30,Narrator,,0,0,0,,ushering in the new era for the Common Path.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:47.42,0:08:54.43,Thought,,0,0,0,,The more influence Soka Gakkai gains in society, \Nthe greater its ability to save the people is,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.43,0:08:58.77,Thought,,0,0,0,,the clearer the attempts \Nto block its progress become.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:58.77,0:09:03.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,It’s all the demons' doing, \Ntrying to stop the spread of the Common Path.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:03.67,0:09:10.94,Thought,,0,0,0,,To confront and fight it, we need to be fully prepared and armed for the battle ahead.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.94,0:09:12.74,Thought,,0,0,0,,And we can't take our time...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:14.10,0:09:15.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,Which means...
Dialogue: 10,0:09:15.71,0:09:19.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,Maybe it’s time I step back \Nfrom day-to-day maintenance {/tending to soka gakkai}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:19.91,0:09:23.60,Thought,,0,0,0,,and focus on laying \Na solid foundation for Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:23.60,0:09:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:25.46,0:09:26.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:27.44,0:09:30.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I have Daito Trading's \Nfinancial results for last month here.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:36.16,0:09:41.29,Thought,,0,0,0,,I don't have to worry anymore. \NYou can walk on your own now.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:41.29,0:09:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, \NI will leave all management to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:46.00,0:09:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I trust you guys to not run it into the ground. {lit: everyone should work hard with the rest}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:48.36,0:09:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:49.96,0:09:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to take this opportunity to retire from all commercial ventures, not just Daito.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:57.12,0:10:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The reasons is because \NI can't stick around forever, you see. {/be with everyone }
Dialogue: 10,0:10:02.40,0:10:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't told anyone yet, \Nbut this is my irrevocable decision.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.42,0:10:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:09.80,0:10:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There’s still a mountain of work ahead for the future of Soka Gakkai and the Common Path.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:17.13,0:10:20.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But sadly, my time isn’t limitless.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:20.79,0:10:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve got to make the most of each day \Nin the little time I have left.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:26.29,0:10:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, I understand what you're trying to say.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:29.50,0:10:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,As you put the final touches on the Common Path,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:32.28,0:10:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,take good care of yourself—\Nand don't feel restrained in all that you do! {/work freely}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:37.72,0:10:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, thank you.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:40.31,0:10:42.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a turning point.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:42.08,0:10:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as a person faces \Nmany life-changing moments,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.60,0:10:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so too do nations and organizations \Nmeet their own turning points.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:49.57,0:10:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,We're standing on one right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:52.40,0:10:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Both for me and for Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.54,0:11:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Shin-chan, take a look.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:04.87,0:11:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The spread of the Common Path \Nnow varies greatly from region to region.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:10.32,0:11:13.17,Default,,0,0,0,,If we keep moving forward \Nwithout considering it,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:13.17,0:11:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the regions with a large number of households will just keep growing.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:16.73,0:11:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But the rural areas with only a handful of households will forever be left behind. {/remain our weak point}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:22.41,0:11:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If left alone, this imbalance \Nwill only get worse over time.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:26.24,0:11:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to me we need to take \Nurgent action—right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:31.88,0:11:33.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The point of most concern
Dialogue: 10,0:11:33.34,0:11:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is the Yamaguchi Prefecture.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:35.53,0:11:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,430 households?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:38.24,0:11:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It's this bad?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:40.37,0:11:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not right...
Dialogue: 10,0:11:42.83,0:11:47.15,Thought,,0,0,0,,There are 2,000 in neighboring Hiroshima,\Nand even in Shimane, at least 1,000 households.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.15,0:11:49.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,Indeed, if this issue isn’t addressed,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:49.53,0:11:54.53,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yamaguchi Prefecture could become the Achilles' heel the Common Path, just as Sensei warned.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.53,0:11:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, we must also tend to mobilizing and strengthening our organization
Dialogue: 10,0:11:59.07,0:12:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in these untapped and underdeveloped regions. \NThis is a turning point, after all.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:07.95,0:12:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say, Shinichi?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.65,0:12:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think you can take the lead \Nat this turning point
Dialogue: 10,0:12:12.42,0:12:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and spark a whirlwind of roundtables \Nand conversions in Yamaguchi Prefecture?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:16.94,0:12:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'll do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:19.01,0:12:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, Yamaguchi Prefecture \Nis the birthplace of the Meiji Restoration.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:24.66,0:12:27.41,Default,,0,0,0,,There are gifted, outstanding men \Nlying dormant there,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:27.41,0:12:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,who can lead the Common Path to greatness. \NI’m sure you can draw them out.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:45.95,0:12:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, how is it going? \NIs this everyone?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:49.20,0:12:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.16,0:12:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's head straight to the base, then.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:52.44,0:12:57.39,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,And so, the “Yamaguchi Campaign”—also called the “Yamaguchi Pioneering Guidance”—
Dialogue: 10,0:12:57.39,0:13:01.99,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,kicked off in Shimonoseki on October 9th, \Nled by Yamamoto Shinichi,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:01.99,0:13:06.81,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,with members and volunteers \Nfrom 32 branches nationwide taking part.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:07.40,0:13:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello! Is everyone doing well?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.21,0:13:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:11.69,0:13:12.42,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:17.17,0:13:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, let's start with a short service.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:21.30,0:13:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}At that time the World-Honored One, wishing to state his meaning once more... {https://nichiren.info/buddhism/lotussutra/text/chap02.html ; 爾時世尊 従三昧 安詳而起…}
Dialogue: 10,0:13:33.25,0:13:38.26,Thought,,0,0,0,,Chief Yamamoto's voice is so lusty, \Nand the tone is reinvigorating!
Dialogue: 10,0:13:38.26,0:13:41.18,Thought,,0,0,0,,So this is how the service supposed to go?
Dialogue: 10,0:13:47.33,0:13:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's read some Scriptures \Nbefore we go out there.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:00.63,0:14:04.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Some person asked Nichiren Daishonin this.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:04.99,0:14:09.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"If your disciples do not understand the Lotus Sutra at all
Dialogue: 10,0:14:09.22,0:14:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and just blindly chant \NNam Myoho Renge Kyo,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:12.00,0:14:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what do such people amount to in a spiritual plane?" That's what the question is. {lit: how much are these people = what's their worth}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:17.42,0:14:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Those disciples are us.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:21.29,0:14:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,The people of Shimonoseki and we still don't fully understand Nichiren Daishonin's Buddhism.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:26.91,0:14:31.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, while chanting before the altar, \None might wonder,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:31.79,0:14:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“What position will this earn me? \NWhat will I gain in the long run?”
Dialogue: 10,0:14:37.19,0:14:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Nichiren Daishonin answers this question as follows:
Dialogue: 10,0:14:41.51,0:14:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,"Those entrusted with this Sutra \Nsurpass all the founders of other sects,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:46.64,0:14:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,were Bodhisattvas of great merit \Nin their past lives,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:51.43,0:14:56.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and are certain to receive boundless blessings in the future."
Dialogue: 10,0:14:56.40,0:14:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No way... {sonna in sanyo dialect}
Dialogue: 10,0:14:57.31,0:14:58.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that true?
Dialogue: 10,0:14:59.11,0:15:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it's hard for you \Nto believe right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:03.24,0:15:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So Daishonin also said...
Dialogue: 10,0:15:13.56,0:15:15.33,Default,,0,0,0,,...before finishing his answer.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:15.81,0:15:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When the Son of Heaven is still a baby, \Ncrying in swaddling clothes,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:20.11,0:15:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,how can you believe that he will one day \Nbecome the Emperor?
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.76,0:15:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,In the same way, we are like babies who know nothing yet and can only believe for now.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:30.74,0:15:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,We may be poor, sick, and have nothing to our name right now—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:35.34,0:15:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but look once more into the scriptures. {unsure what this last part means, maybe "you'll see from now on"; 今は貧乏だったり 病気だったりして あまりぱっとしませんが 今に見ていてご覧なさい}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.77,0:15:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,"They're bound to end up happier \Nand more respected than anyone else in the end.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:43.26,0:15:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what Daishonin guarantees.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:46.72,0:15:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The world may look down on us Soka Gakkai members for now,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:52.68,0:15:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,but as Nichiren Daishonin cautioned, \N“It’s foolish to despise my disciples—
Dialogue: 10,0:15:57.58,0:16:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,they are as precious as the Son of Heaven.”
Dialogue: 10,0:16:02.36,0:16:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need to worry about anything.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.55,0:16:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If you hold the Lotus Sutra in your heart all your life, you will surely be able to lead a fulfilling life. {not a 3-liner}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:11.80,0:16:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s make today a fresh start, \Ngrounded in unwavering faith.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:15.61,0:16:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:22.41,0:16:24.13,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Morning of the 13th.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:24.78,0:16:30.97,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Shinichi arrived to Hofu city and rushed straight to the inn that served as a base.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.97,0:16:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Have no worries.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:33.15,0:16:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We prayed with all our hearts \Nfor the smooth progress of propagation.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:37.97,0:16:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't you agree? \NDon't you feel empowered?
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.64,0:16:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.64,0:16:41.56,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:42.23,0:16:43.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Try to think about it.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:43.78,0:16:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Our fight is that of Buddha's messengers.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:48.08,0:16:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And that fight begins with a sincere prayer.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.40,0:16:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,If we do that, we'll be able to work with a firm resolve
Dialogue: 10,0:16:55.14,0:17:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,to “do whatever it takes to bring forth \Nthe Bodhisattvas of the Earth into this world!”
Dialogue: 10,0:17:00.17,0:17:04.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Only then will the power of Buddha \Nand the Dharma reveal themselves to you.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:04.92,0:17:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:06.71,0:17:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It'll be fine.\NI know you can do it!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:12.28,0:17:17.52,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On the 14th, Shinichi was in Yamaguchi City, \Nthe prefectural capital.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:18.27,0:17:23.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So this is Yamaguchi—the city of history? \NIt sure has a feel all its own.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:23.52,0:17:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's called "Little Kyoto" for a reason.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:32.13,0:17:36.49,Default,,0,0,0,,The Tokugawa clan’s 300-year reign \Nwas secured by subjugating the Chugoku Region—
Dialogue: 10,0:17:36.49,0:17:39.08,Default,,0,0,0,,putting the Mori clan \Nsquarely under their heel. {Chūgoku region (western part of Honshu comprising the prefectures of Okayama, Hiroshima, Yamaguchi, Tottori and Shimane)​}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.08,0:17:45.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If we’re to win the battle for the Common Path, \Nwe’ll have to take Yamaguchi Prefecture first too.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:45.72,0:17:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Our struggle is about opening
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.53,0:17:52.32,Default,,0,0,0,,people’s hearts and minds through compassion and reason, wherever this path takes us.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:52.32,0:17:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s triumph in this Yamaguchi struggle
Dialogue: 10,0:17:54.55,0:17:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,and carve our names into the eternal history \Nof the Common Path!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:58.43,0:17:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.52,0:18:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:59.52,0:18:00.85,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:01.68,0:18:07.98,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,1100)}On the 15th, Shinichi appeared \Nat Koike Inn in Iwakuni City.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:08.85,0:18:12.70,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,{\fade(0,1100)}On the 16th, he was in Yanai City.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:13.78,0:18:17.23,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,And on the 17th, \Nhe arrived to Tokuyama...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:17.24,0:18:19.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief, we're off!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:19.35,0:18:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:20.60,0:18:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Show 'em what's what!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:22.27,0:18:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:24.21,0:18:26.42,Default,,0,0,0,,We should also get to work...
Dialogue: 10,0:18:26.42,0:18:29.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'm looking forward to today's results.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.04,0:18:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. We won't disappoint you! {lit: please wait - idk what to do about it}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:31.42,0:18:32.45,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, later!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:32.45,0:18:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:34.82,0:18:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:36.09,0:18:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,no matter how much we try \Nto lift their spirits, it just isn’t working.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.52,0:18:48.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So why is it that whenever you appear, everyone immediately becomes cheerful and upbeat?
Dialogue: 10,0:18:48.76,0:18:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, I don't have that kind of power.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:52.16,0:18:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I just feel a heightened sense \Nof mission and duty,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:55.49,0:18:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,knowing this might be \Nmy one and only time in Yamaguchi.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:58.65,0:19:03.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s why every time I speak, \Nit’s with the firm resolve to leave my mark
Dialogue: 10,0:19:03.31,0:19:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,on the history of the Common Path here.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.90,0:19:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps everyone else here can sense it too.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:08.48,0:19:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:11.40,0:19:16.72,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,And on the 18th, Shinichi headed to Ube City.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:20.10,0:19:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Ube has a wealth of member households \Nand capable individuals.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:24.48,0:19:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It will be a great hub city in the future.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:27.52,0:19:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,When this month's fighting is done,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:29.80,0:19:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure everyone's selfless work \Nwill show in next month's results. {今月は苦戦に終わったとしても皆さん 存分に戦ったのだから その成果は来月に きっと表れるはずです}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.26,0:19:45.08,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,The general meeting at Korakuen Stadium
Dialogue: 10,0:19:45.08,0:19:49.29,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,was a big success, \Nand we wrapped everything up neatly.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:49.29,0:19:52.79,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,All right, then. It's time to jump back into the fight.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:53.37,0:19:57.30,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,I have to ensure that everyone \NI meet in Yamaguchi is properly trained
Dialogue: 10,0:19:57.30,0:19:59.62,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,to save both themselves and others. {lit: retains his soul; spirit; ghost - dunno what he means}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:59.62,0:20:02.94,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The Yamaguchi Campaign carried on into November,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:02.95,0:20:07.80,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,with Shinichi launching the next phase of activities in Iwakuni City on the 15th.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:08.88,0:20:10.65,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On the following day, the 16th,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:10.65,0:20:15.51,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,he presided over a roundtable discussion at Kaisakuya Inn, the Yanai City base.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:17.66,0:20:25.16,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On the 11th, three women came from Hiroshima, \Nvolunteering to join the campaign efforts.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:25.16,0:20:30.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely, you don't plan to keep fighting \Nfor the entire duration of the campaign? {lit: full schedule; program}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:30.38,0:20:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,No, that's what we wanted to do.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:32.38,0:20:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Unthinkable!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:34.02,0:20:37.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A woman mustn't stay away from home \Nfor such a long time.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:37.40,0:20:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You should return at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:38.65,0:20:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I can't go home.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:42.02,0:20:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband told me not to come back \Nuntil I achieve my goal.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:45.87,0:20:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Same for me! \NPlease allow us to join in the fight.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:48.79,0:20:50.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Please!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:50.03,0:20:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.69,0:20:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gratifying to know that the Okayama Branch \Nsent their very best to support us. {lit: still, okayama branch sure send some of their best - idk what he means, could be [so we don't need you here], but that's a stretch, could be [who are you] but that doesn't make sense - hiroshima is not in okayama, but it's next door, so maybe script error?}
Dialogue: 10,0:20:56.07,0:20:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, how about I write letters \Nto your husbands?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:59.61,0:21:03.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Please write their names and addresses here.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:04.19,0:21:09.65,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Shinichi made it a priority to value \Nand look after each one of his subordinates.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:10.48,0:21:14.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After the battles in Hofu, Ube, and Yamaguchi, Shinichi
Dialogue: 10,0:21:14.40,0:21:19.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,set out for Hagi City on the 20th—\Nthe prefecture’s sole base facing the Sea of Japan.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:19.67,0:21:23.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,So that's Hagi—\Nthe cradle of the Meiji Restoration?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.96,0:21:27.65,Thought,,0,0,0,,"The talented champions of the Common Path \Nmust be in the hiding right now..."
Dialogue: 10,0:21:27.65,0:21:29.39,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's what Sensei said.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.39,0:21:33.75,Thought,,0,0,0,,So how much of that talent \Ncan I awaken from their slumber?
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.75,0:21:36.61,Thought,,0,0,0,,That's what my next battle is going to be!
Dialogue: 10,0:21:44.22,0:21:48.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On the 21st, Shinichi took time between training sessions and propagation
Dialogue: 10,0:21:48.79,0:21:53.24,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to visit Hagi’s historic sites, which preserve the legacy of the Meiji Restoration—
Dialogue: 10,0:21:53.24,0:21:56.22,Narrator,,0,0,0,,a major turning point in Japan’s history. {lit: changing the world; turning the tide restoration}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:02.78,0:22:06.71,Thought,,0,0,0,,An 8 tatami room, a 4.5 tatami room, \Nand a small 3 tatami room... {no idea what he means; probs describing how small this building is}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:06.71,0:22:12.37,ThouTop,,0,0,0,,Sensei told me about it, but it's vastly different from the fancy Meirinkan school facilities. {lit: that han school meirinkan - basically the same thing, and nobody knows what either means anyway (han school is "school established by a daimyo for educating the children of the domain's retainers​); https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Meirinkan - in turn, a rather large organization}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:12.37,0:22:16.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,Still, this place, as small as it may seem, \Nhad produced so many great talents?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:26.51,0:22:28.86,Top,,0,0,0,,Indeed, this little town of Hagi
Dialogue: 10,0:22:28.86,0:22:34.02,Top,,0,0,0,,is where Yoshida Shoin and his students kicked off the whole Meiji Restoration.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:34.02,0:22:34.75,Top,,0,0,0,,However,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:34.75,0:22:37.71,Top,,0,0,0,,Yoshida Shoin wasn’t the only \Ngreat person from here.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:37.71,0:22:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,His disciples were also great, \Nspreading Shoin's name far and wide. {/carrying Shoin's name out into the world}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:42.80,0:22:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They gave their lives for a political revolution.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:45.63,0:22:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,But our goal is a bloodless religious revolution, \Nin which not a single person will die.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:50.77,0:22:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:52.48,0:22:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Although it takes place in a different plane, the master-disciple relationship remains the same.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:58.79,0:23:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Toda-sensei is a unparalleled leader in the religious world.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:03.13,0:23:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the great guide.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:04.84,0:23:10.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If we, his students, don’t at least try \Nto live up to him, then what’s the point? {/measure up to his greatness to some extent }
Dialogue: 10,0:23:10.62,0:23:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like Hagi once raised leaders \Nfor the Meiji Restoration,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:14.35,0:23:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s now our turn to help it \Nproduce champions of the Mystic Law
Dialogue: 10,0:23:19.09,0:23:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,who will fight for peace and happiness \Nof all the people in the world!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:23.88,0:23:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We can only start that process \Nby achieving greatness ourselves!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:28.03,0:23:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:32.43,0:23:36.08,Thought,,0,0,0,,Every base in the prefecture \Nis gaining momentum in the fight,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:36.08,0:23:38.73,Thought,,0,0,0,,and we keep breaking conversion records.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:38.73,0:23:43.98,Thought,,0,0,0,,Organizational development: we're making good progress training and promoting the talents.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:43.98,0:23:46.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,Next time I'll come to Yamaguchi...
Dialogue: 10,0:23:46.82,0:23:49.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,Okay, let's make it January of the next year.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:52.69,0:24:00.45,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The last executives' meeting of the year \Nwas held to conclude the activities of 1956.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:01.01,0:24:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The total number of households \Nconverted in December is 58,694.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:07.03,0:24:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to everyone’s incredible effort,
Dialogue: 10,0:24:09.30,0:24:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ve already blown past this year’s goal of 500,000 households!
Dialogue: 10,0:24:15.89,0:24:21.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And so, the 750,000-household goal \Nthat Toda Josei had set when he took office
Dialogue: 10,0:24:21.81,0:24:24.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was now finally within reach.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:26.46,0:24:31.53,Narrator,,0,0,0,,New Year's Day of 1957.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:31.53,0:24:35.45,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The annual New Year's Service \Nwas held at the Soka Gakkai Headquarters.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:37.06,0:24:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone,
Dialogue: 10,0:24:38.04,0:24:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,what I have here is a New Year's poem\N from Sensei. I shall now read it.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:52.07,0:24:56.58,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'm so glad—Sensei composed \Na poem for the youth division.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:56.58,0:25:00.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's a sign that Sensei has the most appreciation for the youth division. {/loves the ... more than anyone else}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:00.48,0:25:05.88,Thought,,0,0,0,,Our youth division truly are the orcas—\Nstrong and resilient as ever.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:05.88,0:25:11.30,Thought,,0,0,0,,Just look at Shinichi—he showed his endurance\N in last year's Battle for Osaka.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:11.30,0:25:16.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,With Shinichi around, \NI know the youth division is in good hands. {lit: I don't have to worry about training them anymore}
Dialogue: 10,0:25:17.64,0:25:21.40,Thought,,0,0,0,,Before long, the youth Shinichi had raised
Dialogue: 10,0:25:21.40,0:25:23.69,Thought,,0,0,0,,would be like a pod of orcas,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:23.69,0:25:28.72,Thought,,0,0,0,,braving the stormy, wicked seas of the Latter Day of the Law in pursuit of the Common Path.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:29.36,0:25:32.31,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'm looking forward to that time...
Dialogue: 10,0:25:33.41,0:25:37.98,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On January 13th Shinichi flew to Hokkaido
Dialogue: 10,0:25:37.98,0:25:43.10,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,After receiving reports that Soka Gakkai members working in the Yubari coal mines
Dialogue: 10,0:25:43.10,0:25:48.30,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,had faced discrimination and harassment from the mine labor union since last July’s {House of Councillors }election,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:48.30,0:25:51.38,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, serving as deputy head \Nof the Bunkyo Branch,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:51.38,0:25:54.70,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,rushed to Yubari to offer \Nhis encouragement to the workers.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:55.18,0:25:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief, good to see you here!
Dialogue: 10,0:25:57.49,0:25:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no...
Dialogue: 10,0:25:58.12,0:25:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome! {idk}
Dialogue: 10,0:26:00.08,0:26:06.67,Thought,,0,0,0,,Still, it’s kind of hard to believe that 110,000 people live here.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:09.26,0:26:12.30,Top,,0,0,0,,What do you make of the Buddha's position in life? {/circumstances}
Dialogue: 10,0:26:12.30,0:26:14.21,Top,,0,0,0,,There is no poor Buddha.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:14.21,0:26:17.16,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no ailing Buddha.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:17.16,0:26:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no way that you shouldn't be happy too. {/I don't see why you should be unhappy}
Dialogue: 10,0:26:21.33,0:26:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It might feel like people around you are giving you a hard time because of your beliefs,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:26.69,0:26:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's nothing to be afraid of.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:29.57,0:26:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Move forward with the tenacity of a lion king, \Nand stand firm in your faith!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:34.26,0:26:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:44.42,0:26:49.71,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,At last, the Yamaguchi Pioneering Guidance \Nprogram entered its final phase
Dialogue: 10,0:26:49.71,0:26:53.60,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,with a rally in Iwakuni on January 21st.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:53.60,0:27:00.22,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On the 22nd, Shinichi was in Tokuyama, \Nthen in Hofu on the 23rd,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:00.22,0:27:03.81,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,and finally arrived in Ube on the 24th.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:03.81,0:27:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, welcome, Chief!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:06.65,0:27:10.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Branch Chief Okada? \NLooks like the Okayama Branch is raring to go! {okada is fairly common name, so since there is no okada prefecture and he comments on okayama, okada is probably the guy's surname even though there's a historical okada province in the west of Okayama; again, I have no idea what's it even to do with okayama since it's not even neighboring yamaguchi - assuming maybe it's one of the dispatched specialists they mentioned before?}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:10.61,0:27:16.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! I was so excited for your arrival, \NI came out to meet you!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:16.16,0:27:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Our new recruits brought their friends along \Nand are waiting for you at the base.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:21.67,0:27:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Let's hurry!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:27.62,0:27:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:29.15,0:27:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you stay true to your faith, the fulfilling life you’ve dreamed of will surely follow.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:33.94,0:27:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Please proceed with peace of mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:36.07,0:27:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 10,0:27:36.91,0:27:40.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what do you think? \NWill you walk the path of faith with us?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:40.28,0:27:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'll try my best!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:43.33,0:27:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:44.52,0:27:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, I think I'd also give it a shot.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:47.21,0:27:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:49.25,0:27:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, that's a relief!
Dialogue: 10,0:27:54.46,0:27:55.76,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's a mystery...
Dialogue: 10,0:27:55.76,0:27:59.99,Thought,,0,0,0,,He was so opposed to it before,\Nso why was he so easily convinced now?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:59.99,0:28:02.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,It never works this way for me, \Nno matter how hard I try.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:05.28,0:28:06.33,Top,,0,0,0,,Branch Chief Oyama... {again, hoping it's not chief of oyama branch}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:06.89,0:28:09.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we really going to hold a rally \Nat such a large venue?
Dialogue: 10,0:28:09.77,0:28:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's all okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:11.69,0:28:13.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But with so many vacant seats...
Dialogue: 10,0:28:13.59,0:28:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you worry!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:15.72,0:28:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We at Senba Branch have been working really hard to fill this place up. {meaning "working hard to attract new followers who would come to this rally"}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:21.07,0:28:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The Okayama Branch \Nwasn't slacking off either. {still no clue what's it to do with okayama, almost feels like a joke now since their names are okada and oyama}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:23.95,0:28:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, I get it.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:25.91,0:28:30.61,Default,,0,0,0,,That's truly impressive. Just four months ago, \NUbe barely had a dozen households...
Dialogue: 10,0:28:31.11,0:28:32.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:28:31.11,0:28:32.21,Overlap,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:32.21,0:28:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Our growth was so explosive that we'll need to ask for a district to be formed at once. {meaning "advance from a status of a local cell to the status of the district" or something}
Dialogue: 10,0:28:37.30,0:28:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:50.45,0:28:52.50,Thought,,0,0,0,,It's just as Oyama-san said.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:52.50,0:28:55.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,We've completely filled up this large venue.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:55.90,0:29:00.41,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yamaguchi has now firmly joined \Nthe flow of the Common Path. {lit: in the flow of kofu, yamaguchi is no longer an isolated entity}
Dialogue: 10,0:29:00.42,0:29:04.37,Thought,,0,0,0,,I'm sure the Lotus Sutra will keep growing endlessly with its own power
Dialogue: 10,0:29:04.37,0:29:06.47,Thought,,0,0,0,,on this new fertile ground from now on!
Dialogue: 10,0:29:06.48,0:29:14.40,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Yamaguchi Campaign, which spanned three months—October, November, and January—
Dialogue: 10,0:29:14.40,0:29:19.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,led to a tenfold increase in the number of Soka Gakkai households in Yamaguchi Prefecture,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:19.93,0:29:26.25,Narrator,,0,0,0,,from 459 at the end of September \Nto 4,073 by the end of January.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:26.77,0:29:31.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It was a truly great victory, \Nconcluding this Battle for Yamaguchi.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:32.58,0:29:35.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Even in sparsely populated \Nand neglected areas,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:35.44,0:29:40.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,with enough {earnest }cultivation effort, you can turn them into fertile ground for the Common Path. {lit: if you put the sickle deep into the soil }
Dialogue: 10,0:29:40.51,0:29:43.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The resounding success \Nof the Yamaguchi Campaign
Dialogue: 10,0:29:43.49,0:29:46.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,demonstrated to every branch across the country how it's done,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:46.43,0:29:52.48,Narrator,,0,0,0,,leading to an increasing focus on guidance and propagation from local bases.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:52.48,0:29:56.17,Narrator,,0,0,0,,And so, the wave of propagation was now spreading evenly
Dialogue: 10,0:29:56.17,0:29:59.44,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to every nook and cranny of the Japanese archipelago.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:00.36,0:30:04.97,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,But soon after, two unprecedented and monumental incidents occurred,
Dialogue: 10,0:30:04.97,0:30:08.85,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,threatening to destroy \Nthe beautiful unity of Soka Gakkai
Dialogue: 10,0:30:08.85,0:30:11.63,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,and impede the progress of the Common Path.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:12.60,0:30:15.97,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,The "Osaka Incident" \Nand the "Coal Miners Union Issue."
Dialogue: 10,0:30:16.68,0:30:20.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda Josei and Yamamoto Shinichi—\Na teacher and his disciple—
Dialogue: 10,0:30:20.51,0:30:24.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,would once again hurl themselves \Nat the barricades
Dialogue: 10,0:30:24.27,0:30:28.93,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to protect their followers \Nand champion justice for the Soka Gakkai.
